{"doc_id": "hkma_banking_made_easy", "parent_doc_id": "hkma_banking_made_easy", "title": "Banking Made Easy Initiative", "issuer": "Hong Kong Monetary Authority", "authority_level": "regulator", "region": ["Hong Kong"], "topic": ["SME banking", "bank account opening", "digital banking"], "region_code": "HK", "topic_code": "market_entry", "source_url": "https://www.hkma.gov.hk/eng/key-functions/banking/banking-regulatory-and-supervisory-regime/banking-made-easy-initiative/", "document_url": null, "source_type": "HTML", "language": "en", "demo_relevance": "Supports SME onboarding and banking access assumptions in the demo.", "publish_date": null, "effective_date": null, "trust_tier": "regulator", "document_type": "hub_page", "chunk_id": "hkma_banking_made_easy__c0002", "chunk_index": 2, "char_start": 7281, "char_end": 10707, "content": "The HKMA\n\nGovernance Structure Advisory Committees The Chief Executive's Committee Organisation Chart Internal Audit Sustainable HKMA\n\nThe HKMA Information Centre\n\nExhibition Area Library General Information Guided Tours Souvenirs\n\nJoin Us\n\nWhy the HKMA? What We Do? Current Vacancies Opportunities for Students and Graduates to Join the HKMA\n\nTender Invitations\n\nRelated Organisations and Links\n\nHKMA-related Organisations and Links HKSAR Government & Related Organisations Central Banks Multilateral Organisations Others\n\n繁 简\n\nFont Size A A A\n\nPrint\n\nContact Us\n\nHome / Key Functions / Banking / Banking Regulatory and Supervisory Regime / Banking Made Easy Initiative\n\nBanking Made Easy Initiative\n\nAs one of the Smart Banking initiatives announced in September 2017, the Banking Made Easy initiative aims at reducing regulatory frictions hindering technological innovations. A Banking Made Easy Task Force has been set up by the HKMA to identify and streamline regulatory requirements so as to enhance customers’ experience in the following digital customer journeys:\n\nremote customer onboarding and account maintenance;\n\nonline finance; and\n\nonline wealth management.\n\nIn September 2018, the HKMA announced a number of initiatives to further facilitate the development and adoption of regulatory technology (Regtech), commonly referring to the use of technologies for supporting banks’ day-to-day risk management or regulatory compliance processes. The scope of the Banking Made Easy initiative was therefore expanded to also facilitate Regtech development in Hong Kong, focusing on\n\nanti-money laundering/counter-financing of terrorism surveillance technologies;\n\nRegtech for prudential risk management and compliance; and\n\nstudy on machine-readable regulations.\n\nRelated Information\n\nSmart Banking initiatives\n\nPress Release(s)\n\nBanking Made Easy\n\nCircular(s)\n\n03 May 2019\n\nUse of Personal Data in Fintech Development (PDF File, 67.3 KB)\n\n01 Feb 2019\n\nRemote on-boarding of individual customers (PDF File, 71.9 KB)\n\n24 Aug 2018\n\nCircular on Clarification on Remote Investment Account Opening (PDF File, 80.1 KB)\n\n24 Aug 2018\n\nCircular on Online Distribution and Advisory Platforms for Non-SFO-Regulated Structured Investment Products (PDF File, 240.1 KB)\n\n25 May 2018\n\nCircular on Expansion of Types of Life Insurance Products Eligible for Exemption from Financial Needs Analysis (PDF File, 88.8 KB)\n\n09 May 2018\n\nCircular on Credit Risk Management for Personal Lending Business (PDF File, 54.1 KB)\n\n23 Feb 2018\n\nAmendments to Guideline on Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorist Financing (For Authorized Institutions) (PDF File, 69.9 KB)\n\n02 Feb 2018\n\nAnti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorist Financing (Financial Institutions) (Amendment) Ordinance 2018 (PDF File, 76.4 KB)\n\nSpeech(es)\n\n05 Nov 2021\n\nOpening remarks at AML Regtech Lab (AMLab)\nby Carmen Chu, Executive Director (Enforcement and AML), Hong Kong Monetary Authority\n\n21 Jul 2021\n\nOpening Keynote Speech at Fraud and Financial Crime Asia 2021 Conference\nby Carmen Chu, Executive Director (Enforcement and AML), Hong Kong Monetary Authority\n\n30 Jun 2021\n\nClosing remarks at the HKMA's \"Unlocking the Power of Regtech\" Event\nby Arthur Yuen, Deputy Chief Executive, Hong Kong Monetary Authority\n\n30 Jun 2021\n\nOpening remarks at the HKMA's \"Unlocking the Power of Regtech\" Event\nby Eddie Yue, Chief Executive, Hong Kong Monetary Authority\n\n26 Feb 2021", "content_hash": "12f895f3e36e", "chapter": null, "section": null, "page": null}
