se registration\nsystem filing (including\nFIE filing, seal filing, etc)\n1\n3\n2\n4\n5\n6\n7\nPost-registration procedures\nHandle tax registration, tax type\nassessment, etc\nMonthly and quarterly tax filing\nOpening a bank account\n(opening an Rmb basic account, foreign\ncurrency account or other general settlement\naccount at a bank of the enterprise’s choice)\nRegister for foreign exchange\n(register the enterprise’s domestic direct\ninvestment, foreign exchange capital account\nand registration of onshore and offshore credit\nentry at the above-mentioned bank)\nComplete annual business report and joint\nannual report on time\nRegister for social security, provident fund\nand initial staff information entry\n(necessary for companies with staff\nmembers) according to the company’s needs\nCompanies with business operations\ninvolving post-approval must complete\nfiling or obtain a licence from the relevant\nregulatory department before starting the\nbusiness\n\n## Page 12\n\nGoGBA go-to guide\nSetting up a business in the Greater Bay Area (I) - Business registration and business/investment filing\n12\nPreparation\nPost-registration procedures\nRegistration procedures\n1\n12\n6\n2\n13\n7\n3\n14\n8\n5\n10\n11\nInformation for enterprise registration\nIdentity documents of the shareholders, senior\nmanagement and other relevant persons\nProof of rental address\nNotarial certificates for foreign shareholders\nPreparation of other documents and signed materials\nOpening a bank account\nOpening a capital account\nTax registration and reporting\nCompany name pre-approval\nRecord filing for the company’s registered address\nEnterprise registration system filing\n(including FIE filing and seal filing, etc)\nSubmission of the application in hard copy format at\nthe State Administration for Market Regulation\nObtaining the business licence\nObtaining the company seal\nTimetable for registration*\nItem\nTime required\nSubject to investors\n5 working days\n10-20 working days\