{"doc_id": "bsp_financial_inclusion", "parent_doc_id": "bsp_financial_inclusion", "title": "Inclusive Finance", "issuer": "Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas", "authority_level": "central_bank", "region": ["Philippines", "ASEAN"], "topic": ["financial inclusion", "SME finance", "central bank"], "region_code": "PH", "topic_code": "credit", "source_url": "https://www.bsp.gov.ph/SitePages/InclusiveFinance/InclusiveFinance.aspx", "document_url": null, "source_type": "HTML", "language": "en", "demo_relevance": "Supports Philippines SME finance and financial inclusion policy queries.", "publish_date": null, "effective_date": null, "trust_tier": "central_bank", "document_type": "policy_doc", "chunk_id": "bsp_financial_inclusion__c0000", "chunk_index": 0, "char_start": 0, "char_end": 3761, "content": "# Inclusive Finance\n\nInclusive Finance\n\n​ ​​ Share\n\nFinancial inclusion empowers everyone to save, borrow, invest, and thrive. It's not just access - it's a path to better lives and shared prosperity.\n\nFinancial Inclusion\n\nConsumer Protection\n\nEconomic and Financial Education\n\nPERA\n\nscroll left or right to navigate through the tab menu\n\nFinancial Inclusion\n\nNational Strategy for Financial Inclusion (NSFI)\n\nThe NSFI 2022–2028 is a roadmap for advancing financial inclusion to support inclusive growth and financial resilience. Building on the 2015 strategy, it outlines targeted actions, outcomes, and goals to guide stakeholders in accelerating inclusion.\n\n2024 NSFI Annual Report\n\n2023 NSFI Annual Report\n\n2022 NSFI Annual Report\n\nStrategy Document: NSFI 2022-2028 (pdf)\n\nNSFI 2022-2028 AVP (video)\n\nAbout the financial inclusion logo (video)\n\nNSFI 2015\n\nFinancial Inclusion Steering Committee (FISC)\n\nThe FISC is the interagency body guiding the coordinated implementation of the NSFI through policies, regulations, and programs. As mandated by Executive Order No. 208 (2 June 2016), the BSP serves as its chair.\n\nDownload PDF\n\nFinancial Inclusion Regulations\n\nThe BSP promotes financial inclusion by issuing regulations that support innovation and market-based solutions, creating an environment that broadens access to financial services.\n\nRead more\n\nFinancial Inclusion Reports and Publications\n\nFinancial Inclusion in the Philippines\n\nYear-end Reports on BSP Financial Inclusion Initiatives\n\nNational Baseline Survey on Financial Inclusion (NBSFI)\n\n2025 Consumer Finance and Inclusion Survey (CFIS) report\n\n2021 Financial Inclusion Survey report\n\n2019 Financial Inclusion Survey report\n\n2017 Financial Inclusion Survey report\n\nFinancial Inclusion Dashboards\n\nDirectory of Financial Service Access Points\n\nAn informative list of access points to make financial services available and within reach to the public.\n\nRead more\n\nFinancial Inclusion Programs and Advocacies\n\nThe BSP drives programs and advocacies to ensure that the reach of financial services expands to the unserved and underserved segments of the population, especially the country’s most vulnerable. Read more...\n\nPaleng-QR Ph\n\nOpen Finance PH\n\nCredit Risk Database\n\nCredit Surety Fund (CSF)\n\nExternal Financial Inclusion Resources and Engagements\n\nThe BSP actively engages in global and regional forums to advance financial inclusion, sharing knowledge and collaborating with key agencies to support inclusion efforts locally and internationally.\n\nRead more\n\n2023 AFI Global Policy Forum\n\nThe BSP and the Alliance for Financial Inclusion (AFI) co-hosted the 2023 AFI Global Policy Forum\nfrom 12–15 September in Manila. With the theme “Stability, Sustainability, and Inclusivity for Shared\nProsperity,” the event brought together around 800 local and international participants, including\nsenior officials from central banks and financial regulators. AFI is a global network of\ninstitutions from 76 countries advancing financial inclusion for the poor through policy and regulation.\n\nRead more\n\nConsumer Protection\n\nThe BSP Financial Consumer Protection Framework\n\nCircular No. 1048 strengthens consumer protection by making it a core part of governance, culture, and risk management in BSP-supervised financial institutions.\n\nRead more\n\nRelated Videos\n\nMga karapatan at tungkulin ng isang financial consumer\n\nKey Provisions of the Financial Consumer Protection Act\n\nConsumer Assistance Management System (CAMS)\n\nCAMS allows consumers to raise concerns about BSP-supervised financial institutions. It also helps the BSP ensure that BSFIs respond effectively to client needs.\n\nRead more\n\nRelated Video:\n\nAno ang BSP Consumer Assistance Mechanism?\n\nConsumer Assistance Channels and Chatbot", "content_hash": "57f3ddca21b7", "chapter": null, "section": null, "page": null}
