{"doc_id": "boc_global_domestic_lc", "parent_doc_id": "boc_global_domestic_lc", "title": "Domestic L/C", "issuer": "Bank of China", "authority_level": "bank_product_page", "region": ["Mainland China", "cross-border"], "topic": ["letter of credit", "domestic trade financing", "trade settlement"], "region_code": "GBA", "topic_code": "", "source_url": "https://www.bankofchina.com/en/cbservice/cb3/cb34/200807/t20080701_1324130.html", "document_url": null, "source_type": "HTML", "language": "en", "demo_relevance": "Supports L/C and trade settlement explanations.", "publish_date": null, "effective_date": null, "trust_tier": "bank", "document_type": "product_page", "chunk_id": "boc_global_domestic_lc__c0000", "chunk_index": 0, "char_start": 0, "char_end": 1313, "content": "# Domestic L/C\n\ndomestic L/C will be not restricted by customers' credit rating, but they should have the credit line in Bank of China.\n\nProcess\n\n1. The buyer submits the Application for Issuance of L/C to Bank of China , and Bank of China will issue the L/C against the deposit or credit line after approval;\n\n2. After the seller receives the advice of L/C, the advising bank can provide financing service such as packing loan on request of the seller;\n\n3. The seller delivers goods and submits related documents to the transmitting bank under terms of the L/C, the transmitting bank forwards the documents to the issuing bank for payment; meanwhile financing services including the negotiation or bill advance can be provided at the request of the seller;\n\n4. Upon receipt of the documents, the issuing bank makes payment to the seller after examination and approval, meanwhile it can handle bill advance on request of the buyer.\n\n[ Close Window ]\n\nPersonal Banking Login\n\nPersonal Banking(VIP) Login\n\niGTB Corporate Banking Login\n\nInternational Trade Settlement\n\nInternational Trade Financing\n\nDomestic Trade Financing\n\nLetter of Guarantee\n\nSupply Chain Management\n\nSite Map | Contact Us 