angdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\n\nAnnex 1 - Regulatory Requirements on the Southbound Scheme\n\nAnnex 2 - Regulatory Requirements on the Northbound Scheme\n\nAppendix - Frequently Asked Questions on the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect in the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\n\nMemorandum of Understanding\n\n05 Feb 2021\n\nMemorandum of Understanding on the Launch of the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme in the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area between the People’s Bank of China, China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission, China Securities Regulatory Commission, State Administration of Foreign Exchange and the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, Securities and Futures Commission of Hong Kong, Monetary Authority of Macao\n\ninSight Article(s)\n\n04 Aug 2025\n\nEddie Yue on Hong Kong’s Wealth Management Market: Opportunities Ahead\n\n10 Sep 2021\n\nEdmond Lau on Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect in the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\n\n29 Jun 2020\n\nEddie Yue on Wealth Management Connect Scheme in the Greater Bay Area\n\nSpeech(es)\n\n24 Jan 2024\n\nThe Chief Executive of the HKMA’s response on SCIO press conference (Chinese version)\nby Eddie Yue, Chief Executive, Hong Kong Monetary Authority\n\nPress Release(s)\n\n24 Jan 2024\n\nThe HKMA and the PBoC announce measures to deepen the financial cooperation between Hong Kong and the Mainland\n\n28 Sep 2023\n\nEnhancements to the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme Strengthening Financial Market Connectivity in the GBA\n\n27 Jan 2022\n\nThe HKMA announces a list of eligible banks in Hong Kong for launching the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme\n\n18 Oct 2021\n\nThe HKMA announces a list of eligible banks in Hong Kong for launching the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme\n\n10 Sep 2021\n\nHKMA Promulgates Implementation Details for Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme in the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\n\n05 Feb 2021\n\nMemorandum of Understanding on supervisory cooperation under the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect\n\n29 Jun 2020\n\nHKMA welcomes Wealth Management Connect\n\n29 Jun 2020\n\nJoint Announcement of the People’s Bank of China, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, and the Monetary Authority of Macao on the Launch of the Cross-boundary Wealth Management Connect Pilot Scheme in the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\n\n06 Nov 2019\n\nHKMA welcomes the exploring of the establishment of a cross-boundary wealth management connect scheme\n\nContact details for enquiries on Cross-Boundary WMC\n\nhttps://www.hkma.gov.hk/eng/other-information/contact-us/", "content_hash": "782f23642c98", "chapter": null, "section": null, "page": null}
